5:
Damn! It's always when we're in a
rush!
8:
There's no time before the shift is
here! We must push through and
escapeâ€”
19:
A falconer! Thank you, we were truly
in a tight spot for a moment.
22:
Hey, we adventurers have to look
out for each other, yeah? See ya
around!
27:
Where are you going? This place is
about to be consumed by a shift!
You should leave with us!
31:
I appreciate the warning, but I can't
do that. My gramps is still in here!
36: Tch! Guess we've gotta help him!
45:
Adventurers look out for each other,
remember?
57:
Lemarque? You FOOL! What are you
doing here?!
59: As if I'd just leave you behind!
63: Can you still run? We've gotta split!
65:
...I can't, Lemarque. This is my
chance to hop through a shift and
see what other worlds wait out there.
68:
What kinda crazy talk is this? Are
you trying to die?!
73:
Let me GO, Lemarque! I'm riding this
shift, whether you like it or not!
76:
Stop it, Gramps! I'm not gonna let
you throw your life away like that!
79:
Look, I don't know who any of you
people are, but please take
Lemarque out of here!
91:
If you really want to see another
world so badly, there's a safe way to
do it!
102: Haha, I can't believe this is real...
105:
What are we standing around for?
Let's get to exploring!
110:
Gramps! You all right? You know
you're not a young guy anymore,
right...
113:
Argh, growing old is a curse, I tell
you...
116:
I think that's enough excitement for
one day. It's about time we got you
home.
120:
Ah, phooey... Well, at least these old
eyes got to catch a glimpse of
another world.
122:
But I'm the only one with creaking
bones around here. This is your
chance, my boy.
125:
I'm... We're different, Gramps. 
I don't really care about other 
worlds and all that...
127:
Oh, give it a rest. We all know who
you take after.
130:
Sorry to trouble you after everything
you've done, but could you let
Lemarque join your merry band?
134:
W-wait a minute, Gramps! You can't
just throw out a selfish request like
that!
137:
Again with this! You're so terrified of
stepping on people's toes that you
never step anywhere at all!
141:
And YOU'RE always causing people
trouble because you only think
about what you want!
145:
Listen... We've still got tons of empty
rooms, so you're more than
welcome to stay with us.
148:
Just don't tell anyone about
Starview Village, okay?
151:
I promise that your presence will not
be a burden.
153:
Whether or not you wish to join....
Well, that decision is up to you.
158:
...I'll have to pass. I can't leave
Gramps on his own.
160:
WHAT?! Overgrown children
shouldn't worry about adults!
165:
Touched a nerve, eh? Then come
back to me after you've got a few
more feathers in your cap!
168:
Well... I guess the decision's been
made for me.
172:
Sorry about Gramps. But, well... I
mean, if you wouldn't mind...
177:
Welcome to Starview Village,
Lemarque and Kaiser. We're happy
to have you.
186:
Like she said, we're happy to have
you!
190:
And I'm happy to be here! I can't
wait to adventure with you all!
